==English==
===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ʤɜ:k/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɜː(r)k|-ɜː(r)k]]

===Etymology 1===
Apparently imitative.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A quick, often unpleasant tug or shake.
# A sudden, uncontrolled movement, for instance, of the body.
# {{physics}} the [[change]] in [[acceleration]] with respect to [[time]]. 
#: Usage note: Jerk is measured in [[metre]]s per [[cubic]] [[second]] (m/s<sup>3</sup>) in [[SI]] units , or in [[feet]] per cubic second (ft/s<sup>3</sup>) in [[imperial]] units.
# {{slang}} A person, usually male, who is unwelcome due to unlikable qualities and behavior, often mean, foolish or disagreeable.
# A rich, spicy Jamaican [[marinade]]; a [[dish]] made with such a marinade.

